@startuml 09_Rule_Lifecycle
!theme plain
title 3D Data Quality Framework - Rule Lifecycle (State Diagram)

skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BorderColor #90A4AE
  ArrowColor #546E7A
  StartColor #4CAF50
  EndColor #F44336
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF9C4
  BorderColor #F9A825
}

[*] --> DRAFT : User creates rule via Agent\n(validated, trend-scored)

DRAFT --> PENDING_APPROVAL : Submitter != owner\n-> submitted for review

DRAFT --> ACTIVE : Submitter = owner\n-> auto-approved

DRAFT --> [*] : User cancels before\nsubmission

PENDING_APPROVAL --> ACTIVE    : PO / Tech Lead approves
PENDING_APPROVAL --> REJECTED  : PO / Tech Lead rejects\n(reason required)
PENDING_APPROVAL --> DRAFT     : Sent back for revision\n(with feedback)

note right of PENDING_APPROVAL
  SLA Enforcement (Maintenance Job):
  - 24 hr  -> Send reminder to approver
  - 48 hr  -> Escalate to Tech Lead
  - 72 hr  -> Escalate to Data Governance
  - 96 hr  -> Auto-return to DRAFT; submitter
              notified with SLA breach reason
end note

PENDING_APPROVAL --> DRAFT : SLA breach (96 h+)\nauto-returned to submitter

REJECTED --> DRAFT : User revises and\nresubmits (new version)

ACTIVE --> PENDING_APPROVAL    : Rule updated by\nnon-owner (version bump)
ACTIVE --> DISABLED            : Owner / Admin\nmanually disables
ACTIVE --> DEPRECATED          : Superseded by\nnewer version
ACTIVE --> DISABLED_EMERGENCY  : DataOps emergency\nkill-switch

note right of ACTIVE
  Execution Cycle:
  (1) Trigger (schedule / event)
  (2) Read from anomaly_check_config
  (3) Execute SQL (read-only)
  (4) Evaluate violation threshold
  (5) Log to check_execution_log
  (6) Alert on violation
end note

DISABLED --> ACTIVE            : Re-enabled by owner\n+ reason logged
DISABLED --> ARCHIVED          : Inactive for 90+ days\n(auto-cleanup job)

DISABLED_EMERGENCY --> ACTIVE  : Incident resolved\nowner re-enables + post-mortem
DISABLED_EMERGENCY --> ARCHIVED : Permanently retired\nafter investigation

DEPRECATED --> ARCHIVED        : Manually archived\nor auto-cleanup (30 days)

ARCHIVED --> [*] : Deleted after\nretention period (7 years)

note bottom of DISABLED_EMERGENCY
  Instant disable capability for DataOps/Admin.
  Preserves full audit trail -- cannot be deleted
  while in this state. Requires incident ticket.
end note

note left of ARCHIVED
  Archived rules are read-only.
  Accessible for audit/compliance queries.
  Retention: 7 years (configurable).
  Stored in cold Delta table partition.
end note

legend right
  |= Status           |= Execution? |= Editable? |
  | DRAFT             | No          | Yes        |
  | PENDING_APPROVAL  | No          | No         |
  | ACTIVE            | Yes         | Owner only |
  | DISABLED          | No          | Owner only |
  | DISABLED_EMERGENCY| No          | No         |
  | DEPRECATED        | No          | No         |
  | REJECTED          | No          | Yes (revise)|
  | ARCHIVED          | No          | No         |
endlegend

@enduml
